  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Analyzing the Environmental Impact of Fleet Operations of UN Agencies</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UN agencies face an ever-increasing demand for humanitarian operations around the world. Operating in challenging environments and under very variable circumstances, agencies often have no other option to use motorized road transport to reach and serve the beneficiaries that are most in need. Using motorized transport, such as 4x4 vehicles, trucks and motorbikes confront the agencies with a dilemma; whilst providing lifesaving services, their operations also contribute to climate change. As UN agencies seek to reduce their environmental impact from vehicle fleet operations by implementing strategies at global level, a major requirement is to analyse the current environmental aspects and possible impacts and identify environmentally friendly interventions. To address this, the International Organization for Migration (IOM), the leading inter-governmental organization in the field of migration, undertakes, on behalf of the United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP) Sustainable United Nations facility (SUN), the data analysis and preparation of recommendations for selected UN agencies in the area of fleet management.</narrative>
  </description>
